n=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umathildaevazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathildae Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 1:14:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Call to All Paladins and Clerics!</span><hr size=1> No offense, because I think this is a thoughtful idea in theory, but I see this type of &quot;service&quot; being heavily abused. <br><br>I'm interested to see other Cleric/Paladin feedback. <p><b>Mathildae of Vazaelle</b><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7230><b>Profile</b></a><br><a href=http://www.shattered-sorcery.com/blight/index.html><b>Blight</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urobaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 1:24:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> why not?</span><hr size=1> I will check it out, what the heck.  I do rezzes when I can anyway.  I am not sure if this channel is designed for those rezzers who do it to make a little money, for donation, or free.  I agree with Mathildae that this could be problematic, but we will see. <br><br>Robaz<br>Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udurokh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 2:04:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> It will be interesting to see how this works.  As all us rezzers already know, we can get abuse from people we do not rez (for whetever reason).  Will this ease our burdens?<br><br>I rez when I can, but the thought of a worldwide rez channel is a bit unnerving.  Even so, I think I'll pop in just to see what it is like.<br><br>-&gt; Durok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ushylahsoulshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shylah Soulshine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 2:38:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> well.. if anyone ever asks me to travel 5 zones over to give you a 75% rez.<br><br>i will travel across those zones and smack you personally.<br><br>seriously though, i like helping people out... but most people that do a /who all cleric 52 60 looking for a rez think they're owed the rez. then they get all bent outta shape when you say sorry i can't do it.<br><br>but hey, hope the channel works out for you, at least people can bug those that actually want to rez others, and not people in groups <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table><tr><td style="filter:glow(color=FF66CC strength=5);font-family:georgia;font-weight:BOLD;font-size:'10pt'"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20525><font color=#FFFFFF>Shylah</a><br>Knight of Marr<br><i><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/bsynchonline><font color=#FFFFFF>Synch</a>~Vazaelle</font></i></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usupacheal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Supacheal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 3:25:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> Can you ban people out of a channel?  If the clerics stick together and ban people/refuse to res someone who doesn't see it as a request, I think it could work.  Would be no fun to have a quarter of vaz's 50+ clerics and paladins pissed off at you.  Cleric Union~<br><br>Supacheal <p><Img src ="http://www.ghgcorp.com/wduncan/voltron/3dvoltron.jpg" ISMAP> <BR><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42266">My Magelo Profile</A><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukuldiinuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KuldiinUK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 8:06:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> With the introduction of the new rezzes, there are hundreds more clerics available to rez you. <br><br>If your not happy with a 40% rez off a cleric in a zone, because you want a 96% rez from someone in VP, then bad luck for you! <p>Assassin of Vazaelle<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53125" target="main">Kuldiin's Profile </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaurianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 699<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 8:20:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> Though I'm not a cleric on Vazaelle, I will say this....<br><br>I stay out of the Taxi channel. If my cleric were still played, I'd stay out of the Rez channel, too.<br><br><br>For one, people wouldn't use the channel, anyway. Today there were 4 wizards in the taxi channel auctionning that they would go wherever to port, and yet while I was banking/tradeskilling, somebody followed me around Kelethin for 15 minutes hailing me to ask for a port. In the end, people will just do a /who all cle 56 60 just like they always have.<br><br>For two, it's a service that will be abused. The moment you set up a server wide channel expressly for people to go and get a rez, they will think that it's their god-given right to have a rez. You guys take enough crap as it is from people demanding a rez halfway across the world that won't even lift a finger to get you there. (Personally, I offer peridots, and as I'm a wizard I'll port you, too, and TL you wherever you want to go afterwards.) <p><center><a href="http://orderofantondwer.cjb.net" target=_new><image src="http://rkroll.magma.ca/aurie/pics/signature2.gif" alt="My Signature" border=0></a><br><font size=-1>- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21384" target="new">My Magelo</a> - <a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/btheprotectorate9591" target="new">Order of Antondwer</a> - <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter" target="new">Vazaelle Community Center</a> -</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udaerv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daerv</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 8:33:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why not?</span><hr size=1> Personally I don't mind the tells I get. I don't even get that many most days and most rezzes I do are in guild due to ease of communication. I don't set up shop somewhere and go out of my way to make money off rezzes.<br><br>Personally I think a general aid channel would be more use but again its open to abuse. I'd personally like to see the larger &quot;more mature&quot; guilds take responsibility for policing the chat channels to get the idiots out.<br><br>In the end people will send me tells for rezzes and I'll help when I can. So long as they are happy with being turned down or getting no response at all due to I'm in tell hell or I'm busy. Abuse is funny but not altogether pleasant.<br><br>Trouble is, with more rezzes available, more idiots are gonna think its their god given right to get to a rez... <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28162>Daerv Karasu</a><br><a href=http://www.epic-heroes.com>Epic Heroes</a><br><a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161>EH EZBoard</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubeltalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beltalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 1:02:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Call to All Paladins and Clerics!</span><hr size=1> I can see where there could be a benefit to this that hasn't been discussed.<br><br>If clerics willing to do rezzes (for a fee or not at their option) then having them in an "on call" room such as a rez channel could take pressure off clerics who AREN'T available.<br><br>Personally I play mainly a wizard (my cleric is a secondary alt) so, to a much lesser degree, I can appreciate the pain of being pursued by spell-whiners.  My take on it is if a cleric, druid, wizard, or enchanter are anonymous they should NOT be pestered for rez, crack, sow, port.  I don't CARE if you CAN tell what class they are from their pet, equipment, or anything else.  A rez channel might help with this.<br><br>Just an opinion.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udurokh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 2:50:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Call to All Paladins and Clerics!</span><hr size=1> I popped in to rezshop yesterday at 7 PM eastern - only one other person there.  Got out in a hurry.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) -->